$19) 13... Nd3 14. Nd4 Nf5 15. Nxf5 Rae8 $3 $19) ({White is also unable to
solve the problems after} 10. Nd2 Ne5 11. Bb3 (11. Be2 d5 $11) 11... d5 $1 {
once again, the queen on g6 offers dynamic possibilities that allow Black to
simply sacrifice the d-pawn} 12. exd5 Bh3 13. Ne1 Nf5 14. Bf4 (14. Bxb6 $2 Bxg2
$1 15. Nxg2 Nh4 $19) 14... Nd3 $36) 10... axb6 11. Nd2 Ne5 12. Be2 d5 13. f4
N5c6 14. e5 (14. f5 Qh6 15. f6 gxf6 16. exd5 Nxd5 17. Ne4 Be6 $17 {the damage
to Black's pawn structure is not enough to compensate the pawn deficit. Most
importantly, Black maintains lively piece play}) 14... f6 15. exf6 Qxf6 16. Nb3
Qd6 17. Qd2 Bf5 18. Ncd4 Nxd4 19. Nxd4 Be4 $11 {As a general consideration, if
White has lost his e-pawn then Black's opening strategy is likely to have
succeeded. This is not the exception as black enjoys a sound structure and
